奥利弗·斯穆特1962年从麻省理工学院毕业，成为一名律师，后来成为[[美国国家标准学会|美国国家标准学会]]（ANSI）主席<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ansi.org/other_services/speakers_bureau/smoot.aspx?menuid=10 |title=Oliver R. Smoot<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2013-06-25 |archive-date=2013-07-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130729001639/http://www.ansi.org/other_services/speakers_bureau/smoot.aspx?menuid=10 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 和[[国际标准化组织|国际标准化组织]]（ISO）的总裁<ref>[http://www.mit.edu/spotlight/smoot-salute/ MIT - a salute to Smoot<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620132448/http://www.mit.edu/spotlight/smoot-salute/ |date=2015-06-20 }}</ref>。他是诺贝尔经济学奖得主[[乔治·斯穆特|乔治·斯穆特]]的堂兄。<ref name=mitday />

2011年，“斯穆特”作为10,000个新词之一添加到第五版的美国传统词典。<ref>{{cite news|last=Cornish|first=Audie|title=Looking Up Words In A Book Not So Strange Yet|url=http://www.npr.org/2011/11/13/142284657/looking-up-words-in-a-book-not-so-strange-yet|accessdate=10 December 2012|newspaper=National Public Radio|date=2011-11-13|archive-date=2013-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130412075907/http://www.npr.org/2011/11/13/142284657/looking-up-words-in-a-book-not-so-strange-yet|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=smoot&submit.x=47&submit.y=23|work=American Heritage Dictionary|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Publishing Company|title=American Heritage Dictionary entry|accessdate=10 December 2012|archive-date=2014-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512223028/http://www.ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=smoot&submit.x=47&submit.y=23|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==实际使用==
[[Image:100_Smoot_mark.JPG|thumb]]
今天步行过桥的人可以看到标记，表示从人行道到波士顿的河岸有多少斯穆特。标记会每学期由Lambda Chi Alpha重新粉刷。<ref name=haer3>{{cite book
 |author     = Historic American Engineering Record (HAER)
 |title      = Harvard Bridge, Spanning Charles River at Massachusetts Avenue, Boston, Suffolk County, MA
 |url        = http://memory.loc.gov/cgi-bin/ampage?collId=pphhdatapage&fileName=ma/ma1200/ma1293/data/hhdatapage.db&title2=Harvard%20Bridge,%20Spanning%20Charles%20River%20at%20Massachusetts%20Avenue,%20Boston,%20Suffolk%20County,%20MA&recNum=0&itemLink=r?pp/PPALL:@field(NUMBER+@(ma1293))
 |accessdate = 2009-05-12
 |year       = 1987
 |publisher  = Department of the Interior
 |location   = Philadelphia, Pennsylvania
 |id         = http://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/hhh.ma1293
 |page       = 5
}}{{dead link|date=2017年12月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

标记通常每10斯穆特出现，但附加标记会出现在其他数字之间。例如，70斯穆特记号被省略了<ref>[http://flickr.com/photos/iplosion/2875803558/ Photo from the location] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103133752/http://www.flickr.com/photos/iplosion/2875803558/ |date=2012-11-03 }}</ref>；182.2斯穆特标志的伴随着“一半路程到地狱”和指向麻省理工学院的箭头。每个班级也在毕业的年份时加上一个标记。

标记已成为大众所接受。桥在20世纪80年代整修期间，马萨诸塞州剑桥警察部门要求保持标记，因为标记可以确定桥上事故发生的位置。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/1999/hacks-0901.html |title=Keyser describes his top five hacks - MIT News Office<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2013-06-25 |archive-date=2013-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130604013736/http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/1999/hacks-0901.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 翻新者做得更好，因为人行道的混凝土表面上的桥梁间隔为5英尺7英寸，而不是传统的六英尺。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/07/AR2005120702328_pf.html | work=The Washington Post | title=The Measure of This Man Is in the Smoot | first=David A. | last=Fahrenthold | accessdate=2010-05-23 | archive-date=2013-01-20 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6DoelVeYI?url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/07/AR2005120702328_pf.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

Google计算器也采用斯穆特，其估计是67英寸（1.7018米）<ref name=google>{{Cite web |url=http://www.google.com/search?q=1+smoot+in+meters |title=Google: "1 smoot in meters" |accessdate=2013-06-25 |archive-date=2015-06-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150611072239/https://www.google.com/search?q=1+smoot+in+meters |dead-url=no }}</ref>。斯穆特作为一个可选的测量单位加入在[[Google地球|Google地球]]软件和[[Google地图|Google地图]]的测距工具。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://support.google.com/maps/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=1628031 |title=Google Maps distance measurement tool |accessdate=2013-06-25 |archive-date=2013-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524044646/http://support.google.com/maps/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=1628031 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

